                        <div id="faq2" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="faqhead2" data-parent="#faq">
   <div class="card-body">
<ul class="inr_bult">
<li>Wayanad welcomes you to a heaven on earth experience by offering a visual treat that rejuvenates your mind, body and spirit. En route to this land of unrivalled beauty, you will witness the Western Ghats and their lush forests that fosters a sense of peace and relaxation within you.</li>       
<li>From Calicut you can arrive at Jeevess within two and half hours (85 km from the airport). You will go past two districts while seeing the well-known Thamarassery ghats that link Wayanad with Calicut.</li>       
<li>
The route in between will reveal the forest to you accompanied with the chirps and sounds of the birds. You will be amazed by the breathtaking views of Kozhikode from the top of the ninth hair pin bend in the ghats. You can view the Lakkidi view point from the outskirts of the Wayanad district. By going ahead 10 km from Lakkidi, you will reach Vythiri. </li>       
<li>The border district of Wayanad, Kannur connects to the former through various routes for you. Enroute to Jeevess, you will get to see the historic Kottiyoor Palchuram ghat roads while covering a distance of 123 km to Jeevess. You will see the valleys on one side of the road and the other side is full of hills. All in all, it will be a joyous experience while journeying through the green Western Ghats.</li>       
<li> neighbouring state of Karnataka, the border state of Wayanad. The interstate highway connecting Kerala with Karnataka goes straight through Wayanad. Among the multiple routes available for you to travel, the Mysore-Bandipur-Sulthan Bathery route is the best option to reach Jeevess. This route will take you through the Bandipur Tiger Reserve Forest in Karnataka along with Muthanga Wildlife Sanctuary in Kerala leading to Wayanad with an approximate distance 334 km to Vythiry.</li>       
<li>Get ready for the visual feast of nature while moving through the forest, being enchanted by the stillness of it. The second largest wildlife sanctuary in Kerala named Muthanga that shares the borders with Tamil Nadu and Karnataka awaits you there. Muthanga is renowned for its elephant sanctuary. Apart from elephants, you will observe Bison, Tigers and Deer in this forest. </li>       
<li>Once you enter Vythiri, the hometown of Jeevess, you will experience the welcoming climate. The short journey from Vythiri takes you to Jeevess through a route blended with beautiful forest and tea estates and few coffee plantations. You can see a few plantation employees and there are just a handful of families who live nearby. As you slowly drive along the path, watching small water fountains, streams, archaic coffee trees, you might get a surprise welcome by birds, deer or peacocks. </li>       
<li>As you reach Jeevess enjoying the scenery, you can see a wall built with the Jeevess theme that marks that you are reaching your destination.</li>       
     
</ul>
                               
